    {
      "id": 1,
      "name": "good_prompt",
      "prompt": "What are the main approaches to conflict management in work groups? Great. Now apply the most relevant one to a conflict between two cross-functional teams in a tech startup.",
      "response": "Conflict management in work groups can be approached through:\n\n1. Active Listening\n2. Open Communication\n3. Problem-Solving\n4. Negotiation\n5. Mediation\n\nRelevant approach for a conflict between two cross-functional teams in a tech startup: **Negotiation**.\n\nNegotiation involves both parties actively listening to each other, identifying interests and needs, and finding mutually beneficial solutions. In a tech startup, this approach can help teams resolve issues related to conflicting priorities, resource allocation, or differing opinions on project direction.\n\nExample:\n\n**Team A (Product Team)** and **Team B (Design Team)** are working on a project. They disagree on the design of a new feature. Team A wants a simple, user-friendly design, while Team B wants to include more complex features that require more development time.\n\n**Negotiation Process:**\n\n1. **Identify Interests**: Team A and Team B share their concerns and interests. Team A wants to deliver a working product quickly, while Team B wants to showcase their design skills.\n2. **Seek Common Ground**: Team A and Team B explore possible solutions that meet both teams' needs. They discuss potential trade-offs, such as simplifying the feature or using existing design elements.\n3. **Find",
